Climatic adversities braked the economy
In the first year, in which Mario López Valdez at the government is, unemployment and the moonlighting rose in Sinaloa, while the foreign investments decreased and the economy stagnated.
2011 will remain in the economic history Sinaloas in memory. It is the first year, on which Mario López Valdez, which calls itself as the initiator of the change and stirred large hopes up concerning the economic growth, at the government is. However due to the climatic adversities the speech cannot be from growth, but on the contrary the most important economic indicators worsened.
The low temperatures in February did not only cause losses in million height in the agriculture, but put beyond that for the growth of the political economy close borders and caused in the first quarter a general decrease of the economic activity by 3,6 percent of these decrease mainly on the historical dismantling of the agricultural development by 31,16 percent, which braking further sectors of the economy affected.
In accordance with a report on the effects of the Frosts, published from the Consejo Mexicano para el Desarrollo Rural Sustentable (dt. Mexican advice for lasting agricultural development), 582,000 hectares of agriculturally used estates were damaged, about which 78.03 percent perfectly and the remaining 21.07 percent were partly destroyed. Affected were above all the vegetable, corn and cultivation of chickpea.
The decrease of the economic activity until November let unemployment rise in the Mexican state continuously. The Instituto Nacional de Estadística y Geografía observed a fast rise of unemployment in the first quarter, because from January to March 55,053 inhabitants Sinaloas did not have occupation, which corresponds to 4.53 percent of the population of acquisition. In the second quarter the unemployment rate rose to 5,28 percent and from July to Septembers to 6,19 percent, which entails 74,000 unemployed persons in Sinaloa. Those are 18,969 persons more than in the first quarter.
Smaller liquidity
Unemployment in Sinaloa in the year decreases to several factors. The economist Gerardo López Cervantes, dean of the faculty for economic and social sciences of the University of Autónoma (UAS), commentated, the policy of the public institutions explains indirectly increasing unemployment.
“Which we at present observe, are a rise of unemployment, to which with several factors has to do. Among other things with liquidity losses on the market due to the cuts in support by the legislation, which was adopted for the fight of the money laundering in the congress, because for those, which forbid-proves dollar accumulates, it is not easy to let these work for itself it to invest or for otherwise something not use”, explained it.
Migration stopped
López Cervantes pointed out that also a demographic factor is inherent in to increasing unemployment.
“The number of persons, who leave the country on search for work abroad, in particular in the United States, decreased. That is to be due on the one hand to the entry problems and on the other hand, because it is difficult also there work to find. These people remain looking for here and here work, which lets unemployment rise”, means it.
Moonlighting
The analysis of the job market in Sinaloa is still more serious, if one considers the high portion of the moonlighting. This covers 60.38 percent in the country of the persons employed, who work, without depositing into the cashes of the social security in accordance with INEGI.
To unemployment and moonlighting the low wages, the lowest come into all of Mexico, in accordance with the statistics of the Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social (Mexican institute for social security) and the Secretaría del Trabajo y Previsión Social (government authority for work and social welfare service into Mexico).
The average monthly income of the employees in Sinaloa amounted to until Septembers 5352 pesos\; that is very much less as the national average, which is with 7375 pesos.
Decrease of the ADI
Apart from the dismantling of the economic activity and increasing unemployment in the year 2011 the strongest decrease of the foreign direct investment (ADI) of the last ten years is registered. According to Secretaría de Economía (national economic authority) amounted to the ADI from January to June 630,597 dollar, which corresponds to a decrease of 87,74 percent compared with the 5,143,312 dollar in the same period in the previous year.
The Secretaría de Desarrollo Económico del Gobierno (government authority for economic development) registers for its part a total investment at a value of 17,280,000 pesos in the year 2011, which originate first of all from enterprises from the tertiary sector.
The debts
In view of the economic crisis the federal state government requested a credit at a value of 3,000,000,000 pesos, which should be invested for the reactivation of the economy into infrastructure projects in the 18 communities in July at the national congress. The national congress approved an amount at a value of 200,600,000 pesos, however no positive effects of the indebtedness could be determined on any of the industries in the country until November.
Reactions
For the representatives the entrepreneur shank made the first government year Mario López Valdés government inability obvious.
Miguel Loredo López, chairman of the Cámara Nacional de la Industria de la Transformación (national chamber of the processing industry in Mexico) represented the fact that in the year 2011 no efforts toward the harmonization of the opinions of the different sectors including which federal state government, was made.
“The economic activity in Sinaloa was really very poor in this year. It must be worked hard, around which in this year lost terrain to regain and 2012 we must exert doubly. The efforts of all and in particular the progress already government teams joined in well one on the other were co-ordinated not sufficiently one on the other”, explained it.
Slow economic development
Loredo López expressed that events, as the frost made more difficult and slowed the economic development down of the country to beginning of the year.
“The small economic river is the result of several events, among other things the Frosts. One of the most important effects is a slowed down economy, which is not sufficient in motion, in order to cause economic dynamics, which could produce an acceptable river of processes, products and services. Therefore we will conclude, meant the year far below our expectations” it.
Appointment redefine
Teodoro Salazar Uriarte, chairman of the Confederación Patronal de la República Mexicana (trade association of Mexico) in Sinaloa explained, one had to arrange the state to more dynamic productive activities.
“Generally we observed that one worked. We believe that it is necessary a long-term program for the new regulation of the economic appointment and line of the country to develop, because it is importantly all material and human resources Sinaloas to activate”, he said.
There is much to do
The chairman von Coparmex stressed, how important it was to develop a future prospect which directs the efforts of the government into better courses.
“Generally I would say that the government within different ranges obtained good results. The economic development came in front, but it is importantly a long-term program to develop”, explained it.
It stressed that the present power of the state had made progress at the government.
“There are ranges, regarding which one can say that the government acted more comprehensively. Which I can say, it is that it was worked and that the government is conscious that still another quantity of work before it lies, expressed” it.
